&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/972#issuecomment-127182452&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/972#issuecomment-127182452&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Merging this...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14651701" author="githubbot" created="Mon, 3 Aug 2015 10:03:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Github user StephanEwen commented on the pull request:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/972#issuecomment-127182565&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/972#issuecomment-127182565&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    BTW: All of these things are not memory leaks. Java always closes the streams when the objects are garbage collected.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    It is simply good practice to close them as early as possible.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
